if any of you have some insight, if you could share it.<br>
<br>
I, like several other wizzies- put like 1 point into Spec. Evocation back when I was level 20, and left the rest alone.  A couple days ago, I was sitting at the bazaar, you know, doing the &quot;i'm an addict, searching for deals and deals and deals thing&quot; and I decided to take a look at my skills.<br>
<br>
Specialization Evocation: 50 (read: lvl 55)<br>
<br>
So, I'm sitting here wondering what exactly is going on, so I come over to Graffes, and try to do the best I can reading up on Specialization but the site over here and boards aren't agreeing with me that night.<br>
<br>
So, I go to the trainer in Felwithe (I have points left, like 130 or something - <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  and train 1 point into all of the other specializations.  As I'm doing this, they start showing up as...<br>
<br>
Specialization Abjur. : 20 (Feeble)<br>
Specialization Alter. : 20 (Feeble) ..<br>
<br>
blah blah.. you get the point. All at skill level 20, except for Evocation which was already 50.<br>
<br>
So, I sit here and figure to myself, well, it's fixed.  As the next days go on, I'll be nuking more than anything else, and I'll start upping the Spec. Evoc skill.<br>
<br>
I haven't seen a &quot;You have gotten better message (##)!&quot; or anything, and I'm sitting in the bazaar again today, trading languages with some people, which makes me look at my skills, and I see:<br>
<br>
Specialization Abjur: 55 (Average)<br>
Specialization Alter: 55 (Average)<br>
Specialization Div : 55 (Average)...<br>
Specialization Evoc: 50 (Below Average)<br>
<br>
So, now, EVERY Specialization skill EXCEPT Evoc is 55 (and um, that doesn't make sense, becuse I never saw a skill increase message, and the entire day between training and looking later on, I was in Velk's with C2 on, i.e. N00KING), and Evoc is 50, obviously indicating that I've screwed myself somewhere, or I'm the result of some screwed up bug.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts guys? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 2314<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/19/02 7:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weird Specialization situation....</span><hr size=1> You're bugged. I was bugged too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You need to go to the Temple of Solusek Ro and have your specialization skills reset via the quest there. That will reset all your specialization skills to 49. After that, nuke a corspe until Specialize Evocation hits 51, and you'll be all set.<br>
<br>
FYI: This bug seems to happen when you only put one point into Specialization: Evocation and leave the rest empty. Evocation will max out and cap at 50, and once you put points in the other specializations, they will all go over 50 and cap at 55 or so.<br>
<br>
My suggestion is to put points into all of the specializations at level 20, and make sure that evocation hits 51 first. <p><CENTER>
<EMBED src="http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/tegisig01.swf" quality=high bgcolor=#000000  WIDTH="180" HEIGHT="60" NAME="barcode" ALIGN="" TYPE="application/x-shockwave-flash" PLUGINSPAGE="http://www.macromedia.com/go/getflashplayer"></EMBED></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unicolheartsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nicol Heartsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 749<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/19/02 2:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weird Specialization situation....</span><hr size=1> Maybe because you trained at level 55, so the others started at 55 when you put one point into them?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unephyur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nephyur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/19/02 11:36 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weird Specialization situation....</span><hr size=1> Thanks for your words, I think that Jarnin has the issue down, 'cause I talked to a GM today, and he said that any of those skills but one being over 50 is impossible, and this is obviously a corruption bug.<br>
<br>
They have recommended that I speak with a GM about the issue before I try to fix it through the quest, but I'm thinking I'm just going to try to do the reset quest and go from there.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usiryakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/23/02 2:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Heh</span><hr size=1> Step 1: Don't train your spec skills.<br>
Step 2: Get to L 250.<br>
Step 3: Put 1 skill point in each spec.<br>
<br>
Boom!  Uber wizard!<br>
<br>
